<methods>
<methodStep>
<description>
<section>
<para>
<literalLayout>Litterfall collection by litter traps.
Destructive sampling for aboveground biomass estimations of Q. petraea, Q. cerris and Acer campestre. Direct measurement of cut trees and separation of stem, branch and leaf biomasses. 
Allometry equations and tree inventory data (DBH) for estimation of total aboveground biomass of Quercus species.</literalLayout>
</para>
</section>
</description>
<instrumentation>Litter traps for litter production. Destructive harvesting of trees for biomass measurements.</instrumentation>
</methodStep>
<sampling>
<studyExtent>
<description>
<section>
<para>Litterfall was assessed in 2012 using 25 litter traps representing the permanent hectare of the site, with 5.11 m2 total area and was transformed to kg/ha.
Destructive samplings (3-3 individuals of Q. petraea, Q. cerris, Acer campestre) were performed within the LTER site, ~300 m from the 1 ha permanent plot.
Tree inventory (DBH) of the 1 ha permanent plot was used for estimating aboveground biomass of Q. petraea and Q. cerris tree-by-tree and was summed up to kg/ha.
</para>
</section>
</description>
</studyExtent>
<samplingDescription>irregular</samplingDescription>
</sampling>
